description:
PpControlTermination:  Table containing metadata and identifiers for Packet-based control termination points in a radio access network, specifying the location, time, and unique identifiers of each termination.

dateTime: Timestamp of the record.
Area_Name: Name of the geographical area where the termination is located (e.g., NR cell site).
CellId: Unique identifier of the cell where the termination is located.
Id2: Duplicate of CellId.
Id3:  An additional, seemingly redundant, identifier (likely requires further investigation for meaning).
vsDataType:  Data type identifier (likely internal to the vendor's system).
vsDataFormatVersion:  Version of the data format used.
PpControlTermination.ppControlTerminationId: Unique identifier for this specific packet-based control termination.
